to do list for validation:
- length check DONE
- is string check
- is numeric check
- date check
- email validation
- post code validation
- checking if postcode exists (use API)

use good variable names, this is especially needed in tkinter as you are using loads of widgets
e.g:
txt_customer (text)
lbl_customer (label)
btn_customer (button)
lst_customer (list)


use comments on the top of files and next to functions, saying what the main purpose is
####################################################################################
# Name:
# purpose of module:
# bugs or note:
# date:
#####################################################################################

use error trapping
use try and except especially when testing functions, this is to avoid the program crashing



